sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant ModelCtrl as Model Controller
    participant Knative as Knative Serving
    participant Istio as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: Notebook to Model Training to Serving

    User->>Dashboard: 1. Create data science project
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Namespace<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Namespace created

    User->>Dashboard: 2. Create notebook workbench
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI->>NotebookCtrl: Watch Notebook CR
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet + Service<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>NotebookCtrl: Resources created
    NotebookCtrl->>Istio: Create VirtualService<br/>for routing

    User->>Notebook: 3. Develop & train model<br/>OAuth Cookie
    Notebook->>S3: Save trained model<br/>AWS IAM Auth
    S3-->>Notebook: Model saved

    User->>Dashboard: 4. Create InferenceService
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create InferenceService CR<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>KServe: Watch InferenceService CR

    KServe->>S3: Validate model path<br/>AWS IAM Auth
    S3-->>KServe: Model exists

    KServe->>Knative: Create Knative Service<br/>(serverless mode)
    Knative-->>KServe: Service created

    KServe->>ModelCtrl: Notify new InferenceService
    ModelCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Route<br/>for external access
    ModelCtrl->>Istio: Create VirtualService<br/>PeerAuthentication
    ModelCtrl->>Authorino: Create AuthConfig<br/>(optional token auth)
    ModelCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceMonitor<br/>for Prometheus

    Note over KServe,S3: Storage Initializer Init Container
    KServe->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    S3-->>KServe: Model downloaded to /mnt/models

    Note over Client,Istio: Inference Request Flow
    Client->>Istio: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>HTTPS/443 Bearer Token (optional)
    Istio->>Authorino: Validate JWT (if auth enabled)
    Authorino-->>Istio: Token valid
    Istio->>Knative: Forward request<br/>mTLS STRICT (if enabled)
    Knative->>KServe: Route to predictor pod<br/>HTTP/8080 mTLS
    KServe-->>Knative: Prediction result (JSON)
    Knative-->>Istio: Response
    Istio-->>Client: JSON response<br/>HTTPS/443
